He was arrested at the weekend after he allegedly hanged the two girls on Friday at a high school in Stella. JOHANNESBURG – A Potchefstroom teenager is expected to appear in court on Monday for allegedly killing two of his classmates. He was arrested at the weekend after he allegedly hanged the two girls on Friday at a high school in Stella. Teachers discovered one body and alerted police, who found the second body when they arrived at the scene. The police's Amanda Funani says: "A 19-year-old man was arrested in connection with this murder and he’s expected to appear in the Vryberg magistrates court today."